docs.abstract: Paul Krugman Op-Ed column examines how it is possible that health care reform, which has been immense policy success, is largely slipping under the radar; places much of the blame on media and relentless negative political attacks; posits that lack of widespread awareness about impact of the law is due largely to fact that it is the less fortunate who have benefited most.
